<h2 id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3 id="how-do-i-download-gods-of-gravity-from-app-lab">How do I download Gods of Gravity from App Lab?</h3>
<h4 id="download-from-your-mobile-phone">Download from your mobile phone:</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Go to the <a href="https://www.oculus.com/experiences/quest/3919415921458774/">games store page</a></li>
  <li>Log in with your Oculus or Facebook account</li>
  <li>Press the ‚Äúplayer later‚Äù button which will make the game appear in the app library within your headset</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="or-download-from-within-the-headset">Or download from within the headset:</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Open the Oculus explorer or store</li>
  <li>Search ‚Äúgods of gravity‚Äù</li>
  <li>Under the App Lab section of the results, press the ‚Äúview app‚Äù button</li>
  <li>Click on Gods of Gravity and press ‚Äúget‚Äù</li>
  <li>Now the game will appear in your app library and can be installed and launched from there</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="how-do-i-play-gods-of-gravity-with-friends">How do I play Gods of Gravity with friends?</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Launch Gods of Gravity and complete the tutorial, if you haven‚Äôt already (it can be skipped by pressing the menu button on the left controller)</li>
  <li>Once on the main menu, change your username so your friends can identify you by pressing the ‚Äúchange‚Äù button</li>
  <li>Once back the main menu, press the multiplayer button</li>
  <li>If one of your friends has already created a room, click on it to join. Otherwise, create a room for your friends to join by pressing ‚Äúcreate room‚Äù.</li>
  <li>Once all your friends are in the lobby, have the host hit ‚Äústart‚Äù to lock the room and begin setting up the game</li>
</ol>

<p>Note: Rooms are open to all players. If someone joins that you do not want to play with, the host may kick them.</p>

<h3 id="if-i-do-not-have-friends-who-want-to-play-can-i-still-enjoy-the-game">If I do not have friends who want to play, can I still enjoy the game?</h3>
<p>Yes! If you enjoy the social, multiplayer experience, create rooms for others to join or join existing games. Spatial voice chat makes it easy to make new friends in game. Alternatively, play through the single player campaign‚Äôs unique scenarios and unlock new gods which can be used in multiplayer games.</p>

<h3 id="does-gods-of-gravity-have-voice-chat">Does Gods of Gravity have voice chat?</h3>
<p>Yes. Gods of Gravity uses Vivox to deliver high quality spatial audio. Open the in-game menu to mute yourself or any disruptive players.</p>

<h3 id="if-i-get-disconnected-how-do-i-return-to-my-multiplayer-game">If I get disconnected, how do I return to my multiplayer game?</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Quit the game and relaunch it</li>
  <li>Navigate to the multiplayer tab of the main menu by pressing ‚Äúmultiplayer‚Äù</li>
  <li>If the multiplayer game is still active it will appear at the top of the ‚Äújoin a game‚Äù section</li>
  <li>Press ‚Äúrejoin <strong>__</strong>__‚Äôs game‚Äù</li>
</ol>

